properties.areaDesc: Waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River FL out 20 to 60 NM; Waters from Englewood to Tarpon Springs FL out 20 to 60 NM
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 5 at 2:33PM EST until February 6 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, south winds 25 to 30 kt with gusts
up to 45 kt and seas 10 to 12 feet expected. For the first
Small Craft Advisory, south winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to
30 kt and seas 5 to 7 feet expected. For the second Small Craft
Advisory, west winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and seas
8 to 12 feet expected.

* WHERE...Waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River FL out 20
to 60 NM and Waters from Englewood to Tarpon Springs FL out 20
to 60 NM.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 1 PM Thursday to 1 AM EST
Friday. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 1 AM to 1 PM EST
Thursday. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 1 AM to 10 AM EST
Friday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds and seas will pickup throughout the
day on Thursday ahead of an approaching cold front with gale
conditions likely by late Thursday afternoon.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
